text: Neamţ () is a county (judeţ) of Romania, in the historic region of Moldavia, with the county seat at Piatra Neamţ. == Demographics == In 2002, it had a population of 557,000 and a population density of 99/km². *Romanians - 98.66%National Institute of Statistics, "Populaţia după etnie" *Hungarians - 0.05% *Rromas - 1.08 *Lipovans - 0.07%, and others Year County populationNational Institute of Statistics, "Populaţia la recensămintele din anii 1948, 1956, 1966, 1977, 1992 şi 2002" 1948 357,348 1956 419,949 1966 470,206 1977 532,096 1992 578,420 2002 554,516 == References == == Other websites == * www.piatra-neamt.net - Neamt info portal * prefecturaneamt.ro - The Neamt Prefecture * judetulneamt.ro - Neamt county map * neamt.ro - a website about Neamt county * mont.ro - biggest newspaper in Neamt
title: Neamț County
